:R-HSA-418217  a            owl:NamedIndividual , obo:GO_0008150 ;
        rdfs:comment        "Phospholipase C beta (PLCbeta) isoforms are activated by G-protein beta:gamma in the order PLCB3 > PLCB2 > PLCB1. Gbeta:gamma binds to the pleckstrin homology domain of PLC beta, increasing phospholipase activity and leading to increased hydrolysis of PIP2 to DAG and IP3." ;
        rdfs:label          "G beta:gamma signalling through PLC beta" ;
        dc:contributor      "Edited: Jupe, S, 2009-09-09" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: Akkerman, JW, 2009-06-03" , "Authored: Jupe, S, 2009-04-17 08:59:54" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
